x4freetext: Results using ORNL Linac,EXFOR30330
Resonance neutron capture in silicon.
3 MV Van de Graaff accelerator,AAEC Lucas Heights
Li-7(p,n)Be-7, with a 2 ns bunched proton beam
at an energy 15keV above the threshold value of
Natural silicon sample in powder, 827 g(0.098 atom/b),
in a thin magnesium holder(mass 79 g,diam. 15.0cm).
Time of flight.
Techniques used for two-parameter measurement of
neutron capture spectra are described by Kenny et al.,
Austral.J.Phys.27(1974)759.  Emphasis of the experiment
was placed on obtaining gamma-energies to +-1.0keV or
better.
Ge(Li) detector, the efficiency is 14%,
and the resolution is 2.8 keV at 1.33 MeV(gamma).
ORNL-RPI code, Sullivan et al. RPI-328-155(1969) was
used for analysis. This code calculates also self-
shielding and multiple scattering corrections.
for ground state transition for the 35 keV s-wave
resonance.
Al standard target had 15.0 cm of diam. and 0.135atom/b
Gammas.
The present value must be regarded as more accurate
than one of the ORLEA data(EXFOR30330).
Author`s note === The resonance energy of 55.9 keV
which appears in the text and in the Table 2 should be
